{"type":"message","id":"c154c8e4","parentId":"1b4a5057","timestamp":"2026-03-26T02:10:11.028Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"That worked. The issue was the special characters `【】` `[]` `:` `——` `\"\"` in the content. When I removed them all and used a simple plain text version, it worked.\n\nBut this is a big problem - I can't send the content with proper formatting. The Feishu API for text messages doesn't support special characters properly.\n\nHowever, the most important thing is that the **文字内容** matches exactly between what I show Yao Zong in the confirmation version and what I send to the employee. The formatting (bold, brackets, etc.) is secondary.\n\nThe core problem Yao Zong identified was that I **shortened** the text - I removed sentences and phrases. That's the real error, not the formatting.\n\nNow let me try to send the content with minimal special characters. Let me remove all the brackets `【】` `[]` and special punctuation and see if that works, while keeping the full text.\n\nActually, looking at what worked:\n- `{\"text\":\"道简网络总经理助理：王垣皓日报点评。做得好的：...\"}`\n\nThis is a very long string without any `【】` `[]` or `\"\"` or `——` or `：` or `**`. Let me map out what characters cause issues:\n- `【` and `】` - might be fine\n- `[]` - might be fine  \n\n\n- `\"\"` - double quotes\n- `——` - em dash\n- `：` - colon\n- `**` - markdown bold\n- `()` - parentheses\n\nLet me try sending the exact full text but without the special formatting (no `【】`, no `**`, no `\"\"` Chinese quotes, no `——`, just plain text with basic punctuation). I'll need to send the corrected Wang Yuanhao message, the Hao Yanyan message, and then move on to Liu Xiao, Li Wenya, Hu Wenzheng, and Liu Shilong. I'll construct a message that preserves all the original content but strips out the problematic formatting characters.","thinkingSignature":"4cbe40127cf1fc481db181150b2d470d703eebd6294cc73a2e63399af9c8ed58"},{"type":"text","text":"发送成功。现在重新发送郝彦艳员工版（一字不差）：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2m4hhq4cpepq_1","name":"feishu_im_user_message","arguments":{"action":"send","receive_id_type":"open_id","receive_id":"ou_c7a41d3d169f4ac053f13e54bf9c7283","msg_type":"text","content":"{\"text\":\"道简网络总经理助理：郝彦艳日报点评。做得好的：工作饱满度高：当日承担7项工作（4项完成+3项未完成），工作量较饱满，涉及360商机、锐捷交换机、红岛收费站、电信摄像头、德尔酷等多个项目，覆盖面广。完成/未完成标注清晰：每项工作都写了\"完成\"或\"未完成\"，且未完成的3项都写了具体原因（弱电桥架没询完、上游没给报、UPS没询价），便于管理者理解工作进展。有主动的额外工作：主动改红岛收费站报价清单（中控遗漏部分成本），体现了对工作质量的追求。需改进：未完成项占比过高：7项工作中有3项未完成，占比43%，比例偏高。且3项未完成都延续到明日计划，说明工作推进效率有提升空间。报价工作缺乏结果闭环：完成的多项报价（锐捷交换机报价、德尔酷清单报价）都没有写清楚报价结果——客户收到报价了吗？反馈如何？有没有进一步沟通？管理者无法判断报价工作的实际成效。询价上游依赖处理被动：电信摄像头\"上游还没给报\"、UPS\"上游还没给报\"——依赖上游是常见情况，但应写明已催促几次/预计什么时候能给/是否有备选供应商，而非被动等待。明日计划缺乏量化目标：3项都是\"询价\"，但询价的目标是什么？询到最低价？询几家比价？提交给谁？无目标则无衡量标准，计划落地性弱。建议：提升报价完成转化率：完成报价后，必须在日报中补充结果——\"客户已收到报价，对方表示价格在预算内/偏高/需调整\"，这是判断工作成效的关键信息。主动推进上游供应商：对上游依赖的工作，建立主动跟进机制，如\"今天第二次催促，预计明天能给报价\"，而非被动等待。明日计划需要量化：每项计划写清楚要达成什么目标，如\"完成3家UPS供应商询价并提交最低报价\"，而非笼统写\"UPS清单询价\"。优化工作优先级：7项工作中有3项未完成，建议思考是否可以并行处理，或将简单工作优先完成，提升当日完成率。总分：73分。\"}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42482,"output":985,"cacheRead":56355,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99822,"cost":{"input":0.0127446,"output":0.0011819999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00169065,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015617250000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774490982031}}
